                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/487b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-06T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7611. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 434. Embassy’s 9700, April 24, 6 p.m., your 477.<note n="2" xml:id="d289fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> Only 50,000 tons Norwegian sailing vessels available so
                    far. Balance will be forthcoming gradually at later date up to 200,000 tons. All
                    chartered for safe trades, principally east and west coast South America and
                    Australia. Steamer tonnage which they will take place of has already been
                    released from these trades.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
